= <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> Disintegration

The Stegmann dispute marked the beginning of the end for the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span>, as the organization now faces a wave of defections, fund misappropriation, insubordination, and resignations. [+ nsdap_leader +]'s all-or-nothing strategy has proven to be disastrous: the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazi</span> movement has squandered its opportunity.

Instances of the Stegmann revolt are spreading across the nation, first in Hesse, and now among Strasser loyalists in Hamburg and Berlin, who are publicly criticizing Göring and Goebbels for their failed strategy. Ernst Röhm[? if rohm_explode:, now released from prison?], leader of the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span>, has reportedly been considering the idea of the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> declaring independence from the party and pursuing its "own course."

Nonetheless, this is great news! The Reichsbanner and police can finally bring an end to the unceasing political violence plaguing Germany the past years.

