Schleicher had long sought to integrate the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> into the state apparatus. With the organization's rapid collapse, he sees an opportunity to recruit rank-and-file members into a newly formed "self-defense militia" attached to the Reichswehr. However, the Geneva Disarmament Conference has not yet concluded, and any such move would violate the Treaty of Versailles—at least until a formal agreement on rearmament is secured.

In the meantime, the government is creatively re-purposing Germany’s youth for “civilian purposes,” subtly blending their efforts into the broader public works program.